TopicTitle: A lot of part (stock and mods) got category = none

Articles.Content:
In my install environment these parts (see below) got at least "category = none" or even additionally "TechHidden = True" on top - in most cases already in the main part config.

Those parts are not ingame, neither in R&D nor in VAB/SPH.


I can understand the use of "TechHidden = True" for deprecated parts to have the part pack compatible to older career saves.

But these lists?

I'm just curious (and want to have the parts back that are not tagged as deprecated in any way).

In a specific Kerbalism patch I found something that looks sane to me: 

@PART[kerbalism-greenhouse|kerbalism-lifesupport*]:NEEDS[CommunityCategoryKit,!FilterExtensions]:AFTER[zzzKerbalismDefault]
{
	%category = none
}

But other part packs do not check for these conditions:
There is CommunityCategoryKit installed, but there is no FilterExtensions.

 

btw:

https://kerbalspaceprogram.com/api/class_available_part.html#a61573b5ab8745f9cc5a0efe6553f7e9e

If some of those parts are really intended to be deprecated, then I suggest to move them to a folder called deprecated (and edit their paths accordingly).

This not only makes the confusion of users (like me) come to an end, it also makes the devs themselves aware.

If there is a folder full of deprecated files mixed with actual files together and you get "used to it", you just forget stuff and make it complicated.

I just have some parts missing which are perhaps meant to be deprecated in the near future, but the successor parts are not done yet.

I will give this patch a go:

GameData\zFinal\zzz_CCK_move_hidden_parts_to_own_category.cfg 

@CCKExtraFilterConfig:NEEDS[CommunityCategoryKit]
{
	Item
	{
		name = Hidden or deprecated parts
		tag = cck-category-none
		normalIcon = zFinal/cck-category-none/cck-category-none_N
		selectedIcon = zFinal/cck-category-none/cck-category-none_S
		usedByMod = Several mods hide parts
	}
}

@PART[*]:HAS[#category[none],#tags[*]]:NEEDS[CommunityCategoryKit]:FINAL
{
	@tags = #$tags$ cck-category-none
}

@PART[*]:HAS[#category[none],~tags[]]:NEEDS[CommunityCategoryKit]:FINAL
{
	tags = cck-category-none
}

Plus a big question mark as icon.

	icon = cck-category-none

		list = 10,Electrical
		list = 11,Communications
		list = 12,Science
		list = 13,Utility
		list = 14,Undefined

}
